/*! \mainpage SOMA: SOft coarse grained Monte-carlo Acceleration

 \section intro_sec Introduction

 This is the documentation of SOMA it is intended to help to use the
 program. In addition it provides a documentation of the functionality
 of the code. So for developer working with SOMA this is a good
 starting point for anything. If you have nothing developed for SOMA
 before, please read our \ref design page first.

 \subsection Theoretical Background

  The program performs a single-chain in mean-field simulation. For
  further details look for the publication: <a
  href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1063/1.2364506"> "Single chain in mean
  field simulations: Quasi-instantaneous field approximation and
  quantitative comparison with Monte Carlo simulations", Daoulas,
  Kostas Ch. and MÃ¼ller, Marcus , J. Chem.Phys.2006, Volume 125,
  Number 18. </a> <br> For details how this model is implemented in
  SOMA refer also the \ref theory page.

\subsection Detailed Description
